FBIS4-35450 "drnes105_l_94019" FBIS-NES-94-105 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 ISRAEL Commissioner Addresses Knesset on Water Quality Commissioner Addresses Knesset on Water Quality TA0106105394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1000 GMT 1 Jun 94 TA0106105394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el English BFN [Text] Water Commissioner Gid'on Tzur says that autonomy agreements could critically endanger Israel's water supply. In a briefing to the Knesset State Audit Committee, the commissioner said the country's water supply could be damaged by seeping sewage and industrial waste from the autonomous regions. He said he believes that Israel should have secured better guarantees for its water rights during negotiations.
